00:10:57,540 --> 00:11:00,280
x could stand for a one-dimensional coordinate,

291
00:11:00,280 --> 00:11:02,600
it could stand for a three-dimensional coordinate.

292
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:03,580
In fact,

293
00:11:03,580 --> 00:11:05,370
it could even stand for the

294
00:11:05,370 --> 00:11:07,160
coordinates of a large number of particles.

295
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:09,240
And we can just call it space,

296
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:10,640
or coordinate space.

297
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:12,060
Vertically,

298
00:11:12,060 --> 00:11:13,100
we plot time,

299
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:16,360
and the trajectory of a system between two

300
00:11:17,820 --> 00:11:18,380
instants

301
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:22,340
is a curve that goes

302
00:11:22,340 --> 00:11:23,720
from one point to the other.

303
00:11:23,740 --> 00:11:24,500
And then it goes from one point to another curve.

304
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:26,820
And we can call it a world line.

305
00:11:26,940 --> 00:11:27,600
If it's a particle,

306
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:28,780
if it's a single particle,

307
00:11:28,780 --> 00:11:30,480
we call it a world line.

308
00:11:30,740 --> 00:11:33,320
We call it the world line of the particle.

309
00:11:33,580 --> 00:11:36,300
Now this concept is just as good a concept

310
00:11:36,300 --> 00:11:39,020
in non-relativistic physics as it is in relativistic physics,

311
00:11:39,300 --> 00:11:43,550
but it takes a certain primacy in relativity

312
00:11:43,550 --> 00:11:47,800
because of the connection between space and time.

313
00:11:47,880 --> 00:11:49,320
Space and time can morph

314
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:50,760
into each other by Lorentz transformation.

315
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:53,720
We tend to focus more on the space-time connection.

316
00:11:53,740 --> 00:11:55,100
We tend to focus more on the idea of space-time.

317
00:11:56,300 --> 00:12:00,120
The trajectory of a particle is time-like.

318
00:12:00,340 --> 00:12:01,780
Now what do I mean by time-like?

319
00:12:01,900 --> 00:12:05,700
Let's define the notion of time-like.

320
00:12:06,700 --> 00:12:08,640
Begin with just two points.

321
00:12:12,460 --> 00:12:16,180
Begin with any pair of points in space-time.

322
00:12:18,020 --> 00:12:21,520
And think of the separation of the coordinates,

323
00:12:21,520 --> 00:12:24,660
the difference between the coordinates of the two points.

324
00:12:25,060 --> 00:12:26,800
The difference of the coordinates,

325
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:29,860
now I'm speaking about space and time coordinates,

326
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:35,360
we can call them delta t and delta x.

327
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:42,920
I discussed for a couple of times already the

328
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:46,400
notion of the invariant proper time between the two points.

329
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:49,720
And we wrote that as delta t squared.

330
00:12:50,940 --> 00:12:54,770
Delta t squared minus delta x

331
00:12:54,770 --> 00:12:58,600
squared is equal to delta tau squared.

332
00:12:59,520 --> 00:13:01,700
Where delta tau itself,

333
00:13:01,700 --> 00:13:03,320
the square root of this quantity,

334
00:13:03,540 --> 00:13:06,060
is the proper time connecting those two points.

335
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:07,120
Now,

336
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:10,160
this quantity can be positive,

337
00:13:10,380 --> 00:13:12,460
this quantity which I've written delta tau squared,

338
00:13:12,540 --> 00:13:14,440
it can clearly be positive or negative.

339
00:13:14,940 --> 00:13:18,220
It is positive if the,

340
00:13:18,220 --> 00:13:21,740
the separation between these points

341
00:13:21,740 --> 00:13:25,700
is such that the t interval

342
00:13:26,220 --> 00:13:30,560
is larger than the spatial distance between them.

343
00:13:30,740 --> 00:13:31,600
In other words,

344
00:13:33,040 --> 00:13:34,760
if the interval

345
00:13:38,820 --> 00:13:40,040
is like so,

346
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:44,480
if the spatial distance is less than the time distance,

347
00:13:44,780 --> 00:13:46,340
in that case,

348
00:13:46,340 --> 00:13:49,080
delta tau squared is positive,

349
00:13:49,860 --> 00:13:51,780
and the interval between these

350
00:13:51,780 --> 00:13:53,700
two points is called time-like.

351
00:13:54,180 --> 00:13:55,510
It's got more time in it

352
00:13:55,510 --> 00:13:56,840
than it's got space in it.

353
00:13:57,660 --> 00:13:59,560
When an interval is time-like,

354
00:13:59,800 --> 00:14:03,520
you can always find a Lorentz frame of reference.

355
00:14:03,980 --> 00:14:08,000
You can always transform to a frame of reference

356
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:10,980
where the two points are at the same position,

357
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:12,320
where it hasn't moved.

358
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:13,760
In fact,

359
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:15,320
you simply go to the,

360
00:14:16,340 --> 00:14:17,560
to the frame of reference

361
00:14:18,340 --> 00:14:20,280
where this line is at rest.

362
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:22,080
There always exists such a,

363
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:23,380
such a frame of reference.

364
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:24,560
And so,

365
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:27,280
if two points in space-time

366
00:14:27,280 --> 00:14:29,900
are time-like separated relative to each other,

367
00:14:30,040 --> 00:14:32,440
you can always move in such a way

368
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:33,810
that they wind up being

369
00:14:33,810 --> 00:14:35,180
at the same point in space,

370
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:37,560
that they haven't moved relative to each other.

371
00:14:38,320 --> 00:14:38,960
Okay.

372
00:14:39,660 --> 00:14:40,760
That's one case.

373
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:41,940
The other case

374
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:44,960
is where delta x

375
00:14:44,960 --> 00:14:46,480
is bigger than delta t.

376
00:14:48,220 --> 00:14:49,540
In that case,

377
00:14:52,280 --> 00:14:53,600
the separation

378
00:14:54,840 --> 00:14:57,820
has more space interval than time interval.

379
00:14:58,260 --> 00:14:59,360
Looks like this,

380
00:14:59,360 --> 00:14:59,720
let's say.

381
00:15:02,320 --> 00:15:04,620
It's at less than 45 degrees

382
00:15:04,620 --> 00:15:06,440
relative to the horizontal.

383
00:15:07,980 --> 00:15:08,640
Incidentally,

384
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:10,920
I should say right now,

385
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:14,740
when I'm thinking about four-dimensional space-time,

386
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:16,460
three coordinates of space,

387
00:15:16,680 --> 00:15:17,840
one coordinate of time,

388
00:15:18,080 --> 00:15:20,320
what delta x stands for

389
00:15:20,860 --> 00:15:22,960
is the three components

390
00:15:23,839 --> 00:15:26,980
of the vector delta x,

391
00:15:27,100 --> 00:15:29,120
and delta x squared means

392
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:31,320
the sums of the squares of those three components.

393
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:32,710
Delta x squared plus delta

394
00:15:32,710 --> 00:15:33,900
y squared plus delta z squared.

395
00:15:34,540 --> 00:15:35,020
Okay.

396
00:15:35,160 --> 00:15:36,380
I suppose we could,

397
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:37,000
if we liked,

398
00:15:37,100 --> 00:15:39,200
if we wanted to be fancy,

399
00:15:39,460 --> 00:15:41,080
we would put a little arrow over here

400
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:42,740
to indicate that it's a three vector.

401
00:15:43,660 --> 00:15:44,940
That delta x is a three vector.

402
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:46,140
All right.

403
00:15:46,160 --> 00:15:46,220
Now,

404
00:15:46,220 --> 00:15:47,980
if the three vector delta x

405
00:15:47,980 --> 00:15:49,360
is bigger than delta t,

406
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:52,040
then the interval becomes space-like.

407
00:15:53,280 --> 00:15:56,580
Space-like intervals are,

408
00:15:56,700 --> 00:15:57,920
as I said,

409
00:15:57,920 --> 00:15:59,380
are more space than they are time.

410
00:16:00,720 --> 00:16:01,960
And in this case,

411
00:16:02,040 --> 00:16:04,400
you cannot find a reference frame

412
00:16:04,960 --> 00:16:06,660
in which the two points

413
00:16:06,660 --> 00:16:08,620
are at the same position in space.

414
00:16:09,780 --> 00:16:11,040
What you can do

415
00:16:11,040 --> 00:16:13,400
is you can find a reference frame

416
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:14,940
in which they are at the same position.

417
00:16:14,960 --> 00:16:15,220
They are at the same time.

418
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:19,360
You can always find,

419
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:20,120
so that means

420
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:22,820
that there's no invariant significance

421
00:16:22,820 --> 00:16:25,860
to one end being later than the other.

422
00:16:26,100 --> 00:16:28,560
You can always find a frame of reference

423
00:16:28,560 --> 00:16:29,640
in which the two points

424
00:16:29,640 --> 00:16:31,520
are at exactly the same time,

425
00:16:31,740 --> 00:16:33,040
and even worse,

426
00:16:34,040 --> 00:16:35,060
I've drawn this

427
00:16:35,060 --> 00:16:36,900
so that point B,

428
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:38,260
let's call it B and A,

429
00:16:38,920 --> 00:16:41,460
point B appears to be later than point A,

430
00:16:41,620 --> 00:16:43,840
but there exists a reference frame,

431
00:16:43,840 --> 00:16:45,100
this you can work out,

432
00:16:45,140 --> 00:16:46,320
it's very easy to work out,

433
00:16:46,440 --> 00:16:48,300
you can find a reference frame

434
00:16:48,300 --> 00:16:51,440
in which point B is earlier than point A.

435
00:16:52,420 --> 00:16:54,300
So there's no invariant significance

436
00:16:54,300 --> 00:16:56,060
for points which are separated

437
00:16:56,060 --> 00:16:57,700
by space-like interval,

438
00:16:57,960 --> 00:17:00,500
there is no invariant significance

439
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:02,040
to which one occurred first,

440
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,920
one being later than the other,

441
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:06,079
or being simultaneous.

442
00:17:06,520 --> 00:17:08,680
This is the relativity of simultaneity.

443
00:17:09,680 --> 00:17:10,220
Okay.

444
00:17:12,380 --> 00:17:13,460
Particles move,

445
00:17:13,839 --> 00:17:16,359
move on time-like trajectories.

446
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:19,599
Everywhere's along the motion of a particle,

447
00:17:20,599 --> 00:17:22,760
if we break the trajectory up

448
00:17:22,760 --> 00:17:23,839
into little intervals,

449
00:17:25,339 --> 00:17:27,579
every little piece of that trajectory

450
00:17:27,579 --> 00:17:28,460
is time-like.

451
00:17:29,560 --> 00:17:31,640
That's just a statement that particles can't,

452
00:17:31,640 --> 00:17:33,960
nothing can move faster than the speed of light.

453
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:37,060
We've already seen how frustrating it can be

454
00:17:37,060 --> 00:17:38,880
to try to get something to move faster

455
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:39,780
than the speed of light.

456
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:43,220
You try to compile up a whole bunch of velocities,

457
00:17:43,320 --> 00:17:43,820
each of which

458
00:17:43,840 --> 00:17:45,440
is nine-tenths the speed of light,

459
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:45,940
you know,

460
00:17:46,020 --> 00:17:48,960
a stationary observer shoots out something

461
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:50,420
with nine-tenths the speed of light,

462
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:52,880
a moving thing shoots out something else

463
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:54,820
with velocity nine-tenths the speed of light,

464
00:17:54,960 --> 00:17:57,260
something else shoots out a third thing

465
00:17:57,260 --> 00:17:58,840
nine-tenths the speed of light,

466
00:17:58,940 --> 00:18:00,060
you never get anywhere.

467
00:18:00,360 --> 00:18:01,620
It's like Zeno's paradox,

468
00:18:01,900 --> 00:18:02,940
you just get closer and

469
00:18:02,940 --> 00:18:03,980
closer to the speed of light

470
00:18:03,980 --> 00:18:04,960
without ever getting there.

471
00:18:06,020 --> 00:18:08,800
And so it seems like a reasonable hypothesis

472
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:11,760
that nothing ever goes faster than the speed of light.

473
00:18:12,060 --> 00:18:13,380
And that's a good thing,

474
00:18:13,380 --> 00:18:15,280
because it would get very confusing

475
00:18:16,020 --> 00:18:19,160
if we said a particle goes from A to B,

476
00:18:19,340 --> 00:18:20,800
but we can't make sense

477
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:22,260
out of which one is earlier,

478
00:18:22,380 --> 00:18:23,880
the starting point of the particle

479
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:25,240
or the end point of the particle,

480
00:18:25,420 --> 00:18:27,940
we'd get us very confused,

481
00:18:28,220 --> 00:18:31,010
we'd get into all sorts of

482
00:18:31,010 --> 00:18:33,800
questions of time travel and so forth,

483
00:18:33,980 --> 00:18:36,340
but the physical fact is nothing,

484
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:37,640
including a photon,

485
00:18:37,980 --> 00:18:39,820
can move faster than the speed of light.

486
00:18:41,860 --> 00:18:43,160
And I would,

487
00:18:43,380 --> 00:18:45,760
I would generalize that and say that information,

488
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:48,480
information is carried by physical systems.

489
00:18:50,680 --> 00:18:51,200
Signals,

490
00:18:51,220 --> 00:18:54,000
signals that signal information from one place to another

491
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:56,960
can also not propagate faster than the speed of light.

492
00:18:57,380 --> 00:18:58,920
We can take that as a postulate,

493
00:18:59,020 --> 00:19:01,300
but if it were otherwise,

494
00:19:01,700 --> 00:19:03,720
we'd get into some very paradoxical

495
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:06,820
and inconsistent situations.

496
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:08,700
All right,

497
00:19:08,700 --> 00:19:10,680
so that's the notion of time-like and space-like,

498
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:13,240
the notion of the world line,

499
00:19:13,380 --> 00:19:14,260
of a system,

500
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:16,720
and the world line of a system

501
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:19,600
is made up out of small time-like intervals.

502
00:19:20,460 --> 00:19:22,800
Now let's focus on one of those time-like intervals.

503
00:19:24,520 --> 00:19:25,780
Let's redraw it over here.

504
00:19:28,940 --> 00:19:30,580
Here's one of the time-like intervals,

505
00:19:30,740 --> 00:19:32,820
imagine in your head that it's a small interval,

506
00:19:33,399 --> 00:19:35,099
because eventually we're going to let

507
00:19:35,099 --> 00:19:36,800
that interval get smaller and smaller.

508
00:19:37,300 --> 00:19:38,740
I don't think we talked about,

509
00:19:38,980 --> 00:19:40,940
did we talk about relativistic four velocity?

510
00:19:42,060 --> 00:19:42,540
We did.

511
00:19:43,380 --> 00:19:44,000
We didn't do it.

512
00:19:44,020 --> 00:19:45,240
We didn't do it in any detail.

513
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:45,600
All right,

514
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:47,800
so along the trajectory,

515
00:19:48,120 --> 00:19:50,800
the particle moves from one point to another point

516
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:52,400
with a separation delta x,

517
00:19:53,020 --> 00:19:58,160
but delta x is a four-dimensional delta x.

518
00:19:58,260 --> 00:19:59,660
It consists of a delta t

519
00:20:03,940 --> 00:20:09,700
and a delta of the three other coordinates,

520
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:11,020
which are of course called

521
00:20:11,020 --> 00:20:12,240
delta with an arrow above them.

522
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:13,960
That's delta x mu.

523
00:20:15,020 --> 00:20:18,860
Sometimes I will call these spatial delta x's,

524
00:20:19,040 --> 00:20:21,740
sometimes we'll call them delta x i.

525
00:20:22,260 --> 00:20:23,420
When you see an i,

526
00:20:23,420 --> 00:20:25,240
it just runs over space.

527
00:20:25,980 --> 00:20:26,860
When you see a mu,

528
00:20:26,860 --> 00:20:29,640
it runs over all four coordinates of space.

529
00:20:30,120 --> 00:20:35,620
This is an interval along the trajectory here,

530
00:20:35,740 --> 00:20:37,660
has four components to it,

531
00:20:38,380 --> 00:20:41,360
and it defines a delta tau,

532
00:20:43,300 --> 00:20:46,720
between the two endpoints of the interval.

533
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:52,080
Delta tau is equal to the square root

534
00:20:52,080 --> 00:20:57,040
of delta t squared minus delta x squared.

535
00:20:59,520 --> 00:21:00,080
Incidentally,

536
00:21:00,080 --> 00:21:02,360
just once or twice every so often,

537
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:03,560
let's put in the speed of

538
00:21:03,560 --> 00:21:04,720
light just to remember where it goes,

539
00:21:04,980 --> 00:21:06,860
t has units of time,

540
00:21:06,860 --> 00:21:08,100
x has units of space.

541
00:21:08,320 --> 00:21:09,080
To make this thing,

542
00:21:09,080 --> 00:21:12,220
and since this is a,

543
00:21:12,240 --> 00:21:13,500
this is called proper time,

544
00:21:14,139 --> 00:21:16,180
let's assume that it has units of time.

545
00:21:17,420 --> 00:21:18,320
This one's okay,

546
00:21:18,320 --> 00:21:20,220
it has the same units as the left-hand side,

547
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:21,380
but this one is not okay,

548
00:21:21,380 --> 00:21:22,540
it has units of length,

549
00:21:22,660 --> 00:21:23,700
this one has units of time.

550
00:21:23,820 --> 00:21:24,900
Where do we put the speed of light?

551
00:21:26,060 --> 00:21:27,060
Divide by c squared.

552
00:21:29,100 --> 00:21:29,500
Right.

553
00:21:30,220 --> 00:21:31,360
I'll do it now and then,

554
00:21:31,360 --> 00:21:32,340
every so often.

555
00:21:32,820 --> 00:21:34,180
Do it once more over here.

556
00:21:37,139 --> 00:21:38,840
And then stop doing it,

557
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:40,060
because it gets annoying.

558
00:21:42,980 --> 00:21:44,900
Now we have the concept of velocity.

559
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:48,390
Now basic ordinary velocity is the

560
00:21:48,390 --> 00:21:51,460
derivative of x with respect to t.

561
00:21:52,400 --> 00:21:55,340
But there's a notion of four-dimensional velocity,

562
00:21:55,580 --> 00:21:56,420
it is a four vector,

563
00:21:56,420 --> 00:21:58,200
it transforms as a four vector.

564
00:21:58,700 --> 00:22:01,200
Delta x mu transforms as a four vector.

565
00:22:01,560 --> 00:22:04,020
Delta tau is an invariant,

566
00:22:04,020 --> 00:22:04,940
it doesn't transform.

567
00:22:05,020 --> 00:22:06,040
Every observer,

568
00:22:06,040 --> 00:22:07,080
no matter how they're moving,

569
00:22:07,740 --> 00:22:09,300
ascribes the same delta tau,

570
00:22:09,300 --> 00:22:11,680
but different delta x mus to this interval.

571
00:22:14,280 --> 00:22:15,960
The velocity,

